description: Marine Le Pen’s far-right National Rally party was leading in France’s snap parliamentary elections on Sunday with 34% of votes, according to pollster Ipsos Talan.
title: Far-right National Rally leads France's snap poll, left comes second ahead of Macron's camp

description: TEHRAN - Hezbollah Deputy Secretary General Sheikh Naim Qassem has said the resistance movement will respond in kind if Israel launches a full-fledged war against Lebanon.
title: Hezbollah warns Israel against crossing its “red lines”

description: Hezbollah in Lebanon is one of the five superpowers in terms of the number of rockets it possesses, a former Israeli official suggested on Saturday.
title: Hezbollah one of 5 superpowers in rocket stockpile

description: Egyptian President Abdel-Fattah al-Sisi said Sunday that the West Asia region is going through “serious changes" amid a deadly Israeli offensive on the Gaza Strip, Anadolu reported.
title: Sisi: Intl. community silent amid Gaza war
Netanyahu vows to 'eliminate Hamas'

description: Palestine called an extraordinary meeting of the Arab League to discuss Israel’s ongoing war on the Gaza Strip and settlement expansion in the West Bank.
title: Palestine calls for Arab League extraordinary meeting

description: The head of a UK-based medical charity working in Gaza says the health situation has reached a “catastrophic stage” because of the impossibility of acquiring supplies to treat the hundreds of patients flowing into field clinics.
title: Lack of medical supplies leads to ‘catastrophic’ health scenario

description: TEHRAN – The Deputy Speaker of the Islamic Consultative Assembly has highlighted the critical role of voter participation in bolstering national strength, emphasizing that the Iranian nation faces a crucial test in the upcoming runoff election.
title: Iranian MP calls for strong voter turnout in runoff election

description: TEHRAN -In a note, Kayhan addressed the gas contract between Iran and Russia and wrote: Russia's willingness and gas cooperation with this country can be investigated from two aspects.
title: Strategic cooperation between Iran and Russia

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s special envoy to Afghanistan, Hassan Kazemi Qomi, has emphasized the need for thorough consultations with all involved parties due to the complex situation in Afghanistan and the surrounding region.
title: Iran's special envoy highlights the need for comprehensive dialogue on Afghanistan

description: TEHRAN - A top military adviser to Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyyed Ali Khamenei has suggested that Iraq can tap into Iran's extensive 50-year experience in atomic energy.
title: Leader’s advisor offers nuclear collaboration to Iraq

description: TEHRAN - Iran's Deputy Minister of Interior revealed on Sunday that the country's security and intelligence forces successfully thwarted terrorist plots aimed at disrupting the June 28 presidential elections before voting commenced.
title: Terrorists planning to attack polling stations arrested before election day

description: TEHRAN - Mohammad Mokhber, Iran's acting president, has praised the Iranian people for their participation in the June 28 presidential election, asserting that the upcoming runoff vote will prove a disappointment to the Islamic Republic's detractors.
title: Iran's acting president commends voter participation in presidential election

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Guardian Council has officially validated the results of the nationwide presidential election held on June 28th. The announcement, made on Sunday, paves the way for a runoff election scheduled for next Friday, July 5th.
title: Iran's Constitutional Council confirms presidential election results

description: TEHRAN- After Operation al-Aqsa Storm on October 7 and the ongoing war on Gaza, Canada granted Israelis a “humanitarian visa”. According to estimates, thousands of Israelis seized the opportunity and migrated back to the West.
title: Concern over future forces “exodus” from Israel

description: TEHRAN – Iran's acting Foreign Minister, Ali Baqeri Kani, has paid tribute to the victims of the chemical attacks on Sardasht, a northwestern city, which occurred forty years ago.
title: Iran acting FM honors victims of Sardasht chemical attacks

description: TEHRAN - Iran has lodged a formal protest with the United Kingdom over incidents of harassment directed at Iranian voters participating in the country's recent presidential election.
title: Iran demands security measures in protest to UK after harassment of Iranian voters

description: TEHRAN - The fierce controversy surrounding the first televised debate between incumbent US President Joe Biden and former president Donald Trump remains in the limelight days after they locked horns over domestic and global issues.
title: Political scandal

description: TEHRAN- “Three Floors” (“Tre Piani”), a 2021 comedy film by Italian film director Nanni Moretti, was reviewed at the Arasbaran Cultural Center in Tehran on Sunday.
title: Tehran cultural center reviews Nanni Moretti’s “Three Floors”

description: TEHRAN-A collection of detective stories titled “Madam Sara” has been published in Persian by Morvarid Publication.
title: “Madam Sara” detective stories published in Persian

description: TEHRAN-Tehran Museum of Contemporary Art will hold the second session from the series “One Work, One Session,” on July 1, in which a painting by the Spanish artist Antonio Saura will be examined.
title: TMoCA to examine Antonio Saura’s painting

description: TEHRAN-Iranian veteran musician Ardeshir Kamkar and his ensemble will hold a concert at Vahdat Hall in Tehran on July 1.
title: Ardeshir Kamkar to perform Kurdish music at Vahdat Hall

description: TEHRAN-  With the run-off election approaching, the Tehran Times is publishing an overview of the two contenders' opinions about a diverse area of issues. In this section, you can understand the two presidential candidates' views on the most important issues in today's Iran.
title: Where Pezeshkian and Jalili stand on key issues

description: TEHRAN – Fatemeh Hemmati of Iran claimed a silver medal in the Para Archery Ranking series in Czech Republic.
title: Iran’s Hemmati wins silver at Para Archery Ranking series

description: TEHRAN – Saholan Cave, a geological marvel that nature has sculpted over millions of years, has drawn some 61,000 sightseers throughout the first quarter of this Persian year (started on March 20).
title: 61,000 visitors explore Saholan Cave in spring

description: TEHRAN - Shirdal, or griffin, is the name of a legendary creature that features the head and wings of an eagle and the body of a lion. However, a new discovery might change beliefs about this mythical being.
title: Discoveries challenge myths about griffins

description: TEHRAN - Hamedan’s historical and natural allure has captivated more than 1.7 million tourists in the course of the spring season.
title: Hamedan draws 1.7 million sightseers in Q1

description: TEHRAN – An exhibition showcasing a number of modern earthenwares in the form of Ryton, an animal-shaped conical container from which fluids were intended to be drunk or to be poured, has opened doors in Mashhad.
title: Ryton-inspired potteries on show at Khorasan Great Museum

description: TEHRAN - Nestled near the UNESCO-listed Naqsh-e Jahan Square, Isfahan’s carpet bazaar stands as a testament to centuries of tradition, craftsmanship, and cultural heritage.
title: Isfahan’s renowned bazaar of Persian carpets

description: XINJIANG- A number of journalists from some Asian, European, and African countries visited Xinjiang International Grand Bazaar in Urumqi, the capital of China’s northwest Xinjiang Province.
title: Foreign journalists visit Xinjiang International Grand Bazaar

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s Deputy Minister of Agriculture Alireza Mohajer has voiced his country’s readiness to cooperate with BRICS member countries on agricultural sector.
title: Iran ready to cooperate with BRICS members on agricultural sector: Official

description: XINJIANG-  There is no other food that better encapsulates the culture and cuisine of the ethnic group in China’s northwestern Xinjiang province than “Naan”, a baked flatbread.
title: ‘Naan’ encapsulates Xinjiang culture, cuisine

description: XINJIANG- The market of Xinjiang province, in the northwest of China, is very proper for Iran, because there are many cultural similarities between Iran and this region, the secretary of Iran-China Chamber of Commerce told the Tehran Times in an exclusive interview.
title: ‘Xinjiang’s market proper for Iranian product due to many cultural similarities’

description: TEHRAN – A sum of 60 trillion rials (around $100 million) has been allocated to completing semi-finished educational projects by the end of the current Iranian year (March 20, 2025), an official with the Ministry of Education has said.
title: Some $100m allocated to complete semi-finished educational projects

description: TEHRAN –An Iraqi delegation headed by Naeem Al-Aboudi, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, has met Mohammad-Ali Zolfigol, Minister of Science, Research, and Technology, in Tehran on Sunday to discuss the potential for enhancing educational cooperation.
title: Tehran, Baghdad to expand ties in education sector

description: TEHRAN – Head of the National Institute for Oceanography and Atmospheric Sciences has participated in the 57th session of the Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission (IOC) Executive Council.
title: Iran attends 57th session of IOC Executive Council

description: TEHRAN –A delegation from Synergy University of Moscow has paid a visit to Amir Kabir University of Technology in Tehran to explore ways to enhance scientific cooperation between the two institutions.
title: Iranian, Russian universities to foster scientific ties

description: TEHRAN - Iran has purchased some 5.6 million tons of wheat worth over $1.647 billion from domestic producers since April in carrying out a national plan that guarantees the purchase of domestic production of the crop, according to a senior official with the Agriculture Ministry.
title: Iran’s domestic wheat purchase at over 5.6 million tons since April

description: TEHRAN - Pakistan’s Ambassador to Iran Muhammad Mudassir Tipu has said that facilities at two border points between the two countries have been beefed up as part of efforts to facilitate trade and trips by passengers.
title: Pakistan improves facilities at border points with Iran: envoy

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s export of agricultural and food products increased by 29.8 percent in terms of value in the first three months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-June 20), year on year.
title: Agrofood exports increase nearly 30% in 3 months yr/yr

description: TEHRAN – The trade of food and agricultural products between Iran and Turkmenistan increased by 35 percent in the first two months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-May 21), an official with Iran’s Trade Promotion Organization (TPO) said.
title: Exchange of food products between Iran, Turkmenistan rises 35%

description: TEHRAN - Figures by the Central Bank of Iran (CBI) show the country’s hard currency income rose 18.6 percent in the quarter to late June compared to the same period last year.
title: Iran’s hard currency income up 18.6% in Q1: CBI

description: TEHRAN – Iran are ready to participate in the 22nd Asian Women’s U20 Volleyball Championship.
title: Iran ready for 2024 Asian Women’s U20 Volleyball Championship

description: TEHRAN – Iran lost to Samoa 64-59 in the 2024 FIBA U18 Women’s Asia Cup Division B third-place match on Sunday.
title: Iran come third in FIBA U18 Women’s Asia Cup Division B

description: TEHRAN – Iran men’s sitting volleyball team have been invited to the 2024 Men's Sitting Dutch Tournament.
title: Sitting volleyball team to compete at Dutch Tournament
